summary: Served during transion to a unified Somalia, for a period of 5 days. The shortest stint ever as the PM of the republic of Somalia.
Failed in the presidential elections of 1967 which voted out President Adan Abdulle Osman.

Until his participation in Somaliland elections (5th May 1993), when he challenged Mohamed Haji Egal for the presidency, Arte was the defacto PM, even though some reports indicate he resigned in August 1991.
